<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-611-559  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 611 559.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Nov 19 1990 v7 n47 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI will trim 1,500 jobs in major reorganization.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp is announcing a major reorganization thatwill cut costs and allow the company to be more responsive tostiff competition and customer demands.andP;  The company will fold itsseven regional service divisions, resulting in the dismissal of1,500 employees.andP;  The service divisions, responsible for bothresidential and business services, are to be replaced by the newConsumer Markets unit, Business Markets group and Network Servicesgroup.andP;  Analysts contend that AT and T's increasingly aggressivemarketing efforts as well as the worsening economy have made itmandatory for MCI to improve its operating efficiencies.andP;  Theyalso believe that survival in this competitive marketplacerequires a market-driven organizational structure.andP;  Both AT and Tand US Sprint Communications Co are also restructuring to bettermeet customer needs and improve operating costs.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (Layoffs)US Sprint Communications Co. (Management)American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Management).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     LayoffReorganizationCost ReductionMarket AnalysisGoals and Objectives.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>